      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SUGAR DROP BABY (5) turned spotting a big start finishing eighth (16.74) last time in a Grade 5 at The Gardens. Solid record here winning two races. Good beginner but will need a little luck from a middle draw. Better than the latest effort and deserves another chance. LIPSCHITZ (3) filled a minor placing last start at this track behind Flying Minter (18.04) in a Grade 5. Led around the bend before fighting on well and should give a sight. Smart beginner who should take advantage of the low draw. Leading player again. TABLOID GOSSIP (2) showed little early speed at her last couple, the latest finishing eighth (18.43) in a Grade 4 at this track. Safe beginner who has drawn to advantage. Will give the top chances plenty to think about. IMPRESS BEV (1) missed the placings here last start but is well-placed to make amends.",
